<paragraph blockId="26.[178,1085,1402,1454]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1539">
D i a g n o s i s: Distinguishable from superficially similar specimens of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="1539">
<taxonomicName authorityName="OPITZ" authorityYear="1997" box="[994,1085,1402,1423]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Pilosirus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="1555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pilosirus</taxonomicName>
brunoi
</emphasis>
by having a smaller antennomere 5 (compare 
<figureCitation box="[714,836,1432,1454]" captionStart="Figs 70-80" captionStartId="21.[178,218,1351,1373]" captionTargetBox="[178,1100,235,1309]" captionTargetId="figure-1@21.[178,1100,212,1333]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 70-80: Antennae. (70) Isoforma fritilla, female; (71) I. goryi, female; (72) Isoforma planata, female; (73) Pilosirus brunoi, male; (74) Isoforma subgilva, female; (75) Pilosirus amazonicus, female; (76) P. fasciatus, female; (77) Platynoptera carti, male; (78) P. flavohumeralis, male; (79) P. humeralis, male; (80) P. lyciformis, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5294864" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5294864/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="1539">Figs. 73, 76</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[178,1086,1469,1608]" lastBlockId="27.[178,1085,219,299]" lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="1540" pageId="26" pageNumber="1539">
D e s c r i p t i o n: Size: Length 7.0 mm; width 2.0 mm. Form: As in 
<figureCitation box="[920,1009,1469,1491]" captionStart="Figs 161-164" captionStartId="52.[178,218,1513,1535]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,212,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-59@52.[178,1085,212,1498]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="Figs 161-164: Habitus illustrations of (161) Pilosirus fasciatus, holotype; (162) P. versus, holotype; (163) Platynoptera carti, holotype; (164) Platynoptera flavohumeralis, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5282519" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5282519/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="1539">Fig. 161</figureCitation>
. Color: Cranium black; pronotum mostly black, upper sides flavotestaceous; mesoscutellum black; elytra mostly black, humeral angle and mid-elytral fascia flavotestaceous. Head: Antennal capitulum long (
<figureCitation box="[448,525,1557,1579]" captionStart="Figs 70-80" captionStartId="21.[178,218,1351,1373]" captionTargetBox="[178,1100,235,1309]" captionTargetId="figure-1@21.[178,1100,212,1333]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 70-80: Antennae. (70) Isoforma fritilla, female; (71) I. goryi, female; (72) Isoforma planata, female; (73) Pilosirus brunoi, male; (74) Isoforma subgilva, female; (75) Pilosirus amazonicus, female; (76) P. fasciatus, female; (77) Platynoptera carti, male; (78) P. flavohumeralis, male; (79) P. humeralis, male; (80) P. lyciformis, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5294864" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5294864/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="1539">Fig. 76</figureCitation>
), each capitular antennomere not as long as combined length of funicular antennomeres; antennal carina very prominent; EW/FW 10/13. Thorax: Pronotal anterior margin not projected at middle, side margin of disc with obtuse tubercle; PW/PL 40/40; elytral disc not strongly deflexed at sides, carina not present; EL/EW 170/35. Abdomen: Female pygidium not incised at distal margin.
</paragraph>
